    <td id="maintext">        <div id="cptitle">About Cal Parents</div>
        <!-- closing div for id="cptitle" -->
        <h3>A Welcome to Parents and Families</h3>
        <p>With a student at UC Berkeley, you've joined an amazing, lively, 
          diverse community. Before our  students enrolled, we each knew about Berkeley's 
          unsurpassed reputation for teaching, research, and public service &#8212; 
          the reputation that drew us to the campus in the first place. What we 
          didn't expect was Berkeley's commitment to help, engage, and involve 
          us as parents. </p>
        <p>The Cal Parents program is the centerpiece of that commitment. Advised 
          by a board of more than 70 parents and supported by an incredibly dedicated 
          staff, the program offers the resources and referrals you need to support 
          your student's education at Berkeley. Cal Parents keeps us up 
          to date on all the campus has to offer &#8212; from our experience, 
          that's had a real benefit on our kids as students.</p>
        
        <p>Cal Parents works to keep the parent-student-university partnership strong 
        and vital. In addition to this web site, we'll be in touch through 
        <a href="/about/dates.shtml">campus and regional events</a>, 
        <a href="/about/helplines.shtml">telephone and e-mail helplines</a>, 
        the <a href="http://www.berkeley.edu/calparents/letterhome/">Letter Home 
        newsletter</a>, and the <a href="http://www.berkeley.edu/calparents/guide/">Resource Guide for Parents </a>. We also reach out to parents to encourage their involvement 
        and support in these ways:</p>
        <!-- closing div for class="hilite" -->
        <ul>
          <li>Facilitating parent-to-parent communications</li>
          
        <li>Urging financial support for UC Berkeley through <a href="/gifts/index.shtml">The 
          Cal Parents Fund</a> </li>
          <li><a href="http://alumni.berkeley.edu/services/advocacy">Advocating</a> 
            for UC Berkeley in Sacramento and Washington, D.C.</li>
          <li>Recruiting volunteers for Cal Parents events and activities</li>
          <li>Providing input to the campus administration.</li>
      </ul>
        The college years are among life's highlights &#8212; the time when our 
        sons and daughters put our years of nurturing into practice as independent 
        adults. On behalf of Cal Parents, we invite you to join us in making the 
        most of the exciting years ahead. 
      <p><br>
      Amelia Kaymen (Mom to son Thomas '13)<br>
      Richard Steiny '79 (Dad to daughters Samantha '13 and Peri '15)<br>
      Cal Parents Co-Chairs for 2012-13</p>
        </div></td>
    <!-- InstanceEndEditable --> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="sidebar" -->
